  <entry xml:base="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/deuteronomy-7-9/">
    <title>Deuteronomy 7:9</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/deuteronomy-7-9/"/>
    <id>https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/deuteronomy-7-9/</id>
    <published>2026-05-25T16:46:09-05:00</published>
    <updated>2026-05-25T16:46:09-05:00</updated>
    <category term="fighter-verses" label="fighter-verses"/>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;This week, our family is memorizing &lt;strong&gt;Deuteronomy 7:9&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.fighterverses.com/verse-index&#34;&gt;Fighter Verses: Set 1, Week 1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;parallel-verse-container&#34;&gt;
    
  &lt;div class=&#34;verse-col english-col&#34;&gt;
    &lt;header class=&#34;col-meta-header&#34; role=&#34;button&#34; tabindex=&#34;0&#34; aria-label=&#34;Toggle Focus Mode&#34; onclick=&#34;toggleColumnFocus(this)&#34; onkeydown=&#34;if(event.key===&#39;Enter&#39;||event.key===&#39; &#39;){toggleColumnFocus(this); event.preventDefault();}&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-label&#34;&gt;CSB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;col-zoom-status-icon&#34;&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-expand&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M15 3h6v6M9 21H3v-6M21 3l-7 7M3 21l7-7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-collapse&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M4 14h6v6M20 10h-6V4M14 10l7-7M10 14l-7 7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/header&gt;
    
    &lt;div class=&#34;verse-content-body&#34;&gt;Know that the LORD your God is God, the faithful God who keeps his gracious covenant loyalty for a thousand generations with those who love him and keep his commands.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-cite&#34;&gt;Christian Standard Bible (Nashville, TN: Holman Bible Publishers, 2020), Dt 7:9.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&#34;verse-col hebrew-col&#34;&gt;
    &lt;header class=&#34;col-meta-header&#34; role=&#34;button&#34; tabindex=&#34;0&#34; aria-label=&#34;Toggle Focus Mode&#34; onclick=&#34;toggleColumnFocus(this)&#34; onkeydown=&#34;if(event.key===&#39;Enter&#39;||event.key===&#39; &#39;){toggleColumnFocus(this); event.preventDefault();}&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-label&#34;&gt;Hebrew&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;col-zoom-status-icon&#34;&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-expand&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M15 3h6v6M9 21H3v-6M21 3l-7 7M3 21l7-7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-collapse&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M4 14h6v6M20 10h-6V4M14 10l7-7M10 14l-7 7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/header&gt;
    
    &lt;div class=&#34;verse-content-body&#34;&gt;וְיָ֣דַעְתָּ֔ כִּֽי־יְהוָ֥ה אֱלֹהֶ֖יךָ ה֣וּא הָֽאֱלֹהִ֑ים הָאֵל֙ הַֽנֶּאֱמָ֔ן שֹׁמֵ֧ר הַבְּרִ֣ית וְהַחֶ֗סֶד לְאֹהֲבָ֛יו וּלְשֹׁמְרֵ֥י מִצְוֹתָ֖ו לְאֶ֥לֶף דֹּֽור׃&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-cite&#34;&gt;K. Elliger, W. Rudolph, and Gérard E. Weil, Biblia Hebraica Stuttgartensia, electronic ed. (Stuttgart: German Bible Society, 2003), Dt 7:9.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- &lt;div class=&#34;verse-col greek-col&#34;&gt;
    &lt;header class=&#34;col-meta-header&#34; role=&#34;button&#34; tabindex=&#34;0&#34; aria-label=&#34;Toggle Focus Mode&#34; onclick=&#34;toggleColumnFocus(this)&#34; onkeydown=&#34;if(event.key===&#39;Enter&#39;||event.key===&#39; &#39;){toggleColumnFocus(this); event.preventDefault();}&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-label&#34;&gt;LXX&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;col-zoom-status-icon&#34;&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-expand&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M15 3h6v6M9 21H3v-6M21 3l-7 7M3 21l7-7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
            &lt;svg class=&#34;zoom-icon-collapse&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;13&#34; height=&#34;13&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2.5&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M4 14h6v6M20 10h-6V4M14 10l7-7M10 14l-7 7&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/header&gt;
    
    &lt;div class=&#34;verse-content-body&#34;&gt;καὶ γνώσῃ ὅτι κύριος ὁ θεός σου, οὗτος θεός, θεὸς πιστός, ὁ φυλάσσων διαθήκην καὶ ἔλεος τοῖς ἀγαπῶσιν αὐτὸν καὶ τοῖς φυλάσσουσιν τὰς ἐντολὰς αὐτοῦ εἰς χιλίας γενεὰς&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;col-meta-cite&#34;&gt;Septuaginta: With Morphology, electronic ed. (Stuttgart: Deutsche Bibelgesellschaft, 1979), Dt 7:9.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; --&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/deuteronomy-7-9/&#34;&gt;Continue reading &amp;#10230;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</content>
  </entry>
  <entry xml:base="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/five-ways-the-word-purifies-us/">
    <title>Five Ways the Word Purifies Us</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/five-ways-the-word-purifies-us/"/>
    <id>https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/five-ways-the-word-purifies-us/</id>
    <published>2026-05-11T18:45:00-05:00</published>
    <updated>2026-05-11T18:45:00-05:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Robert Purnell lists five ways that God&amp;rsquo;s Word purifies His saints:&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Word is purifying (John 15:3). You are clean through the Word that I have spoken to you. Now, the Word purifies in several ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As an antidote against sins. &amp;ldquo;Your word have I hid in my heart, that I might not sin against you&amp;rdquo; (Ps. 119:11).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a lamp discovering the spot. &amp;ldquo;I had not known sin but by the law&amp;rdquo; (Rom. 7:7).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a star conducting to Christ, the fountain of purifying (1 John 2:1-2; Zech. 13:1).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a rule, according to which we are heedful to order our conversation: &amp;ldquo;Wherewith shall a young man cleanse his way, but by taking heed thereto, according to your word?&amp;rdquo; (Ps. 119:9).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a motive in the precious promises of it: &amp;ldquo;Having therefore these promises, let us cleanse ourselves from all filthiness of the flesh and spirit&amp;rdquo; (2 Cor. 7:1).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;footnotes&#34; role=&#34;doc-endnotes&#34;&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li id=&#34;fn:1&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Robert Purnell, &lt;em&gt;A Body of Doctrinal and Practical Divinity from 1657&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;https://freegracepress.com/products/a-body-of-doctrinal-and-practical-divinity-from-1657&#34;&gt;Free Grace Press&lt;/a&gt;, 2026), 82.&amp;#160;&lt;a href=&#34;#fnref:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-backref&#34; role=&#34;doc-backlink&#34;&gt;&amp;#x21a9;&amp;#xfe0e;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/five-ways-the-word-purifies-us/&#34;&gt;Continue reading &amp;#10230;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</content>
  </entry>
  <entry xml:base="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/william-perkins-on-preaching/">
    <title>William Perkins on Preaching</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/william-perkins-on-preaching/"/>
    <id>https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/william-perkins-on-preaching/</id>
    <published>2026-04-06T19:16:28-05:00</published>
    <updated>2026-04-06T19:16:28-05:00</updated>
    <category term="preaching" label="preaching"/>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;The elements of preaching, as summed up by William Perkins in 1592:&lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preaching involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reading the text clearly from the canonical Scriptures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explaining the meaning of it, once it has been read, in the light of the Scriptures themselves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gathering a few profitable points of doctrine from the natural sense of the passage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the preacher is suitably gifted, applying the doctrines thus explained to the life and practice of the congregation in straightforward, plain speech.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The heart of the matter is this:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;https://joshua.poehls.me/2026/william-perkins-on-preaching/&#34;&gt;Continue reading &amp;#10230;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</content>
  </entry>
  <entry xml:base="https://joshua.poehls.me/two-ways-to-not-use-a-bible-reading-plan/">
    <title>Two Ways To Not Use A Bible Reading Plan</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://joshua.poehls.me/two-ways-to-not-use-a-bible-reading-plan/"/>
    <id>https://joshua.poehls.me/two-ways-to-not-use-a-bible-reading-plan/</id>
    <published>2022-03-29T07:52:10-05:00</published>
    <updated>2022-03-29T07:52:10-05:00</updated>
    <category term="scripture" label="scripture"/>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s the idea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You want to read your Bible in roughly a year. Or at least you want to make steady progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t like being tied to a specific reading plan. You like the flexibility to pick what book to read next.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You want to make sure you actually &lt;em&gt;do&lt;/em&gt; read through the whole Bible. Without a plan, it is easy to end up rotating through your favorite books and avoid others longer than you realize.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If that sounds like you, I have two strategies that may help. I&amp;rsquo;ve been using one of these for a couple years now, and the other is fairly recent.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;https://joshua.poehls.me/two-ways-to-not-use-a-bible-reading-plan/&#34;&gt;Continue reading &amp;#10230;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</content>
  </entry>
