  <entry xml:base="https://joshua.poehls.me/2018/resources-for-studying-zephaniah/">
    <title>Resources for Studying Zephaniah</title>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://joshua.poehls.me/2018/resources-for-studying-zephaniah/"/>
    <id>https://joshua.poehls.me/2018/resources-for-studying-zephaniah/</id>
    <published>2018-11-14T13:41:40-05:00</published>
    <updated>2018-11-14T13:41:40-05:00</updated>
    <category term="scripture" label="scripture"/>
    <category term="tim-mackie" label="tim-mackie"/>
    <category term="jason-derouchie" label="jason-derouchie"/>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve been studying through Zephaniah recently, prompted by the recently released &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amazon.com/ESV-Expository-Commentary-7-Daniel-Malachi/dp/1433546523?&amp;amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;amp;tag=poehls-20&amp;amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;amp;linkId=f84fa13acb18f9e11c227fc183537e37&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=9325&#34;&gt;ESV Expository Commentary (Volume 7): Daniel–Malachi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. The commentary on Zephaniah is written by Jason DeRouchie who I&amp;rsquo;ve been following since his &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amazon.com/How-Understand-Apply-Old-Testament/dp/1629952451?&amp;amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;amp;tag=poehls-20&amp;amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;amp;linkId=3aea9f4d4504f9ceb5bb219392214716&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=9325&#34;&gt;How to Understand and Apply the Old Testament&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;, which is fantastic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aside:&lt;/strong&gt; Andy Naselli&amp;rsquo;s companion volume, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.amazon.com/How-Understand-Apply-New-Testament/dp/1629952486?&amp;amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;amp;tag=poehls-20&amp;amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;amp;linkId=1b2956844e522127703e788ed3967077&amp;amp;camp=1789&amp;amp;creative=9325&#34;&gt;How to Understand and Apply the New Testament&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;, is equally fantastic. I read it first and I&amp;rsquo;m still working through DeRouchie&amp;rsquo;s volume.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;span&gt;&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;https://joshua.poehls.me/2018/resources-for-studying-zephaniah/&#34;&gt;Continue reading &amp;#10230;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</content>
  </entry>
